  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This package documents a credibility assessment for a CFD hemolysis prediction model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to evaluate absolute hemolysis levels under ventricular assist device operating conditions. Seven of thirteen ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed; the remaining six are flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across the full operating envelope. All assessed factors achieved their required credibility levels under the Minimal profile submission. The model is considered credible for supporting engineering decisions in the context in which it has been exercised, as described in the narrative above. No structured ContextOfUse object is provided under this Minimal profile submission.",
